President Obama has named 94 researchers as recipients of the Presidential Early Career Awards for Scientists and Engineers, which is the highest honor given by the US government to science and engineering professionals in the early stages of their careers. The awards recognize the researchers' innovative work and commitment to community service. The recipients come from various federal departments, including Agriculture, Commerce, Defense, Education, Energy, Health and Human Services, Interior, Transportation, Veterans Affairs, Environmental Protection Agency, NASA, and the National Science Foundation.